{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad470125-87ad-43f8-a495-27e0a8d74183","content":"## What happened\n\nDSA was marked obsolete (`SYSLIB0039`) starting in .NET 7, and .NET has been progressively removing platform-specific DSA support. On macOS, `DSA.Create()` now throws **`PlatformNotSupportedException`** because Apple's native crypto frameworks (Security.framework / CryptoKit) dropped DSA entirely — and .NET on macOS relied on those native libraries. Windows and Linux still work because their crypto backends (CNG and OpenSSL, respectively) still support DSA.\n\n## How to fix it\n\nSince you only need to **verify** legacy signatures (not produce new ones), the cleanest cross-platform fix is to use **BouncyCastle**, which is a pure managed implementation with no native-library dependency:\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\nThen replace the platform-dependent `DSA.Create()` call:\n\n```csharp\n// Before (.NET 10) — throws on macOS under .NET 11\nusing System.Security.Cryptography;\n\nbool Verify(byte[] data, byte[] signature, DSAParameters keyParams)\n{\n    using var dsa = DSA.Create();       // PlatformNotSupportedException on macOS\n    dsa.ImportParameters(keyParams);\n    return dsa.VerifyData(data, signature, HashAlgorithmName.SHA1);\n}\n\n// After — works everywhere via managed code\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Signers;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Math;\n\nbool Verify(byte[] data, byte[] signature, DSAParameters keyParams)\n{\n    var p = new DsaPublicKeyParameters(\n        new BigInteger(1, keyParams.Y),\n        new DsaParameters(\n            new BigInteger(1, keyParams.P),\n            new BigInteger(1, keyParams.Q),\n            new BigInteger(1, keyParams.G)));\n\n    var signer = new DsaDigestSigner(\n        new DsaSigner(), new Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Digests.Sha1Digest());\n    signer.Init(false, p);\n    signer.BlockUpdate(data, 0, data.Length);\n    return signer.VerifySignature(signature);\n}\n```\n\n## Long-term recommendation\n\nDSA is considered legacy; plan a migration to **ECDSA** or **Ed25519** when you control the signing side. Until then, BouncyCastle gives you a portable, fully-managed DSA verifier on all three platforms.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"33d7b878-8467-4cf7-ae5f-5954171ef538","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS when upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me reason about this from my knowledge.\n\nThis is a known breaking change in .NET. Starting with .NET 7+, Microsoft has been progressively removing older/insecure cryptographic algorithms. Specifically, DSA support on macOS has been affected because Apple's Security framework (and CommonCrypto/CryptoKit) dropped DSA support, and .NET on macOS relied on Apple's native crypto libraries.\n\nIn .NET 7, there was a breaking change where `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS because Apple removed DSA support from their security frameworks. \n\nI should clarify the timeline here—the user mentions upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11, which would be happening around late 2025 to early 2026. The DSA issue on macOS actually originated back in .NET 7, so this isn't a new problem introduced between these versions, but rather a longstanding limitation that persists. I'm realizing the core issue is that DSA was marked obsolete in .NET 7 and progressively removed, particularly on macOS where Apple's native crypto libraries don't support it—so `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException`. The main workarounds are using a managed implementation like BouncyCastle for signature verification, installing OpenSSL via Homebrew, or migrating to a modern algorithm like ECDSA or RSA. The root cause is that .NET 11 completely removed DSA support on macOS since Apple's security framework doesn't provide it and .NET dropped the managed fallback. I'd recommend using BouncyCastle for cross-platform DSA verification, or switching to ECDSA/EdDSA if possible.","outputTokens":1749},"id":"05d78137-d3fd-4233-8dc3-ac2b29657c0d","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:58:00.623Z","parentId":"d18a0055-a394-40b3-bf29-bb5872c0ff7b"}
